# shadcn/ui + Tailwind (apps/web)

- Components live under `apps/web/src/components/ui/` (copied from shadcn, not an npm design-system package).
- Use existing `Button`, `Card`, `Table`, `Badge`, `Sheet`, `Input` primitives before adding new UI dependencies.
- Style with Tailwind utility classes; follow mobile-first responsive layout.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class names.
- Keep presentational components thin; data fetching belongs in hooks (`useResponses`, `useSocket`, `useIncidents`), not in table/badge primitives.
- Prefer accessible patterns: semantic HTML, labels on inputs, meaningful button text.
